# ihsm protocol — Config bag pattern (0.1.1)

Each actor defines a single **`MachineConfig`** interface (e.g. `CBServerMachineConfig`) with:

| Bucket | Purpose | Examples |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `context` | Domain data mutated from state handlers only | `ICBServerContext` |
| `notifications` | Client commands (`notify.start()`) | `start()`, `stop()` |
| `services` | Client queries (`call.initialize()`) — return values or throw | `initialize(): Promise<void>` |
| `internalNotifications` | Environment `on*` + internal `do*` sequencing | `onSpawn()`, `doProcessNext()` |
| `port` | Outbound impurity (spawn, stdin, timers via `hsm.port`) | `spawn()`, `stdinFor()` |

State classes extend **`ihsm.TopState<MachineConfig>`** — one generic only.

## Handler APIs (0.1.1)

- `this.hsm.transition(StateClass)` — not `this.transition()`
- `this.notify.event()` / `this.notifyNow.event()` — not `post` / `postNow`
- `this.hsm.port.spawn()` / `setTimeout()` — not `this.port` on handlers
- `this.hsm.currentStateName` / `this.hsm.currentState`
- Services return `Promise<T>` or throw — no `ResolveCallback` / `RejectCallback`
- `makeActor` returns `ExternalActor`; child subactors use `makeChildActor(asParentActor(this), …)` or `makeActor` with parent `InboundActor` ref
- Production ports: `this.actor.notify.onSpawn()` — not `inbound.post`
- Parent forwards to child: `child.notify.onData(chunk)` — not `readerPort.send`
- `await child.call.initialize()` — not `call("initialize")`
- `ctx.serverMailbox = this.hsm.port.actor` in `initialize`

## Allowed in public protocol

| Kind | Examples | Posted by |
|------|----------|-----------|
| **Commands** (`notifications`) | `start()`, `stop()` | Clients (`main.ts`, extension, tests) |
| **Queries** (`services` / `call`) | `initialize`, `subscribeStatus`, `getCurrentStateName` | Clients — never `call` / `sync` inside state handlers |
| **Environment `on*`** (`internalNotifications`) | `onSpawn`, `onData`, `onProcessExit`, `onDisconnect` | Outside world only (subprocess, network). Use `onProcessExit` not `onExit`. |

## Forbidden in public protocol

- Internal scheduling glue (`doProcessNext` belongs in `internalNotifications`, not `notifications`)
- Port method names on the protocol (those belong on `Config.port` / `Port` subclass)

## Handler placement

- **Top state** — services only on leaves that handle them. No environment `on*` on root unless inherited.
- **Omit** a protocol method on a state to inherit from parent.
- Shared subprocess IO → `ProcessObserving`; lifecycle → leaf states (`Starting`, `Stopping`, …).

## State classes (Node servers)

- Mark initial leaf with `@ihsm.InitialState` on the state class.
- Call `ihsm.registerStateNames(self)` at the bottom of each machine module (`import * as self from "./…"`).
- Enable `experimentalDecorators` in package `tsconfig.json`.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — single Config generic
export class CBServerTop extends ihsm.TopState<CBServerMachineConfig> {}

// ✅ GOOD — promise service
async initialize(): Promise<void> {
  this.ctx.serverMailbox = this.hsm.port.actor;
  this.hsm.transition(Initialized);
}

// ❌ BAD — old 0.0.x positional generics
export class CBServerTop extends ihsm.TopState<Ctx, Public, Internal, Port> {}
```
